<p>Bruce &#8211; as Piketty says, out wealth data is incredibly bad. I&#8217;m not going to assume bad faith in any attempt to take a closer look at Picketty&#8217;s findings in that respect. Because the data is so bad, I think it&#8217;s certainly possible, if unlikely, that we&#8217;re not seeing much of an increase in wealth inequality in some cases.*</p>
<p>Our income data, on the other hand, is good enough to declare anyone who doubts that income inequality is increasing in the UK (and almost all other advanced industrialized countries) outside of fact-based discourse. </p>
