<p><i>. . . hidden. Does anyone know?</i></p>
<p> if anyone knew, it wouldn&#8217;t be hidden, would it?</p>
<p>A great deal of wealth is hidden in plain sight, in the sense that the totals or the income streams are more or less known, just the equities are hidden, but some of the big numbers are attached to contingencies that really obscure who owns what.  That&#8217;s what derivatives do and the numbers there are huge.  Piketty argues, I believe, that one of the reasons to impose wealth taxes is to clarify the equities.</p>
