<p>I&#8217;m sorry but none of this makes sense. r&gt;g actually doesn&#8217;t imply what Piketty says it implies and it certainly doesn&#8217;t shed any light on why &#8220;increasing wealth is a bad thing for society&#8221;, and neither is it empirically well founded. It is unfortunately an immense distraction away from the empirical accomplishment of Piketty&#8217;s work, I assume born out of the desire to be seen as a theoretician rather than &#8220;just&#8221; a data cruncher. What people (e. g. Krugman) now take away from it is the entirely misconceived idea that we need to focus even more on raising g by any means possible.</p>
