<p>Rakest @44<br />
1. Exports are not the point. Net exports are the point (and remember the J-Curve adjustment, where initial movements may be in the wrong direction)<br />
2. Yes, currency politics are a problem which why the whole disfunctional international financial system needs (which has caused the problem) needs to be sorted out. <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2008/nov/18/lord-keynes-international-monetary-fund" rel="nofollow">http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2008/nov/18/lord-keynes-international-monetary-fund</a><br />
