<p>Btw it&#8217;s on page 3 that Piketty says that the &#8220;sustained demographic growth&#8221; that people were seeing in the late 18thC and 19thC was &#8220;a previously unknown phenomenon&#8221;. I don&#8217;t know whether it has any impact on his overall thesis, because I haven&#8217;t got much further than that yet! But I do think it may be oversimplification of the sort Bruce Wilder identified (for some reason my iPad is not letting me cut and paste, but that really nice intro at 104 about the imagined &#8220;foggy sort of homogeneity&#8221; of the past). </p>
